goal_checkin_teen_data.troubleshooting.problems.3.tip:
🌷 You may need to spend more one-on-one time with your teen.

⭐ Give more positive attention to them when they are behaving well and praise them for this behaviour.

🌙 Be patient. Learning to manage our behaviour takes time!
If you are feeling overwhelmed or angry, take a deep breath. If needed, walk away from the situation before you react. 
;
Remember, your teen’s behaviour isn’t meant to hurt you. As teens, it's normal for them to explore their limits. 

A sudden increase in misbehaviour may sometimes be a warning sign. Type {HELP} if you need support for your teen.

If your teen is misbehaving consistently, type {GROW} to learn more about their behavior, or check out these resources:

{structure resources}

{mental health resources}

